.TH "calc_rc_params" 9 "calc_rc_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calc_rc_params \- reads the user's cmdline mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" calc_rc_params
.BI "(struct rc_params *rc "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_dsc_config *pps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rc" 12
DC internal DSC parameters
.IP "pps" 12
DRM struct with all required DSC values
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function expects a drm_dsc_config data struct with all the required DSC
values previously filled out by our driver and based on this information it
computes some of the DSC values.

\fInote\fP This calculation requires float point operation, most of it executes
under kernel_fpu_{begin,end}.
